tafsir[15]{c,v,t}:
  15,72,"By your life - O Messenger - the people of Lot wander blindly in pursuit of their lusts."
  15,73,"The destructive punishment seized them at the time of sunrise."
  15,74,"We turned their towns upside down and rained on them a shower of petrified clay."
  15,75,"In the incident mentioned about the punishment that descended on the people of Lot there are signs for those who ponder."
  15,76,"The towns of the people of Lot are on an existing road and can be seen by travellers who pass by."
  15,77,"In that which occurred there is a sign for the believers to take lesson from."
  15,79,"We took retribution from them when the punishment seized them. The towns of the people of Lot and the dwellings of the people of Shuayb are on a path clear to those who pass by."
  15,81,"We gave them proofs and signs to indicate his truthfulness in what he brought from his Lord. One of these was the she-camel. But they did not take a lesson from those signs and paid no attention to them."
  15,82,"They used to carve out dwellings in the rocks of the mountains in which they lived safe from that which they feared."
  15,83,"Then the bolt of the punishment seized them in the morning."
  15,84,"The wealth and the dwellings that they had gained did not ward off Allah’s punishment."
  15,87,"We have given you ‘The Opening (Sūrah Al-Fātiḥah)’ which consists of seven verses and We have given you the Grand Qur’ān."
  15,88,"Do not extend your sight to the temporary enjoyments We have given to some classes of disbelievers and do not grieve over their rejection. Be humble with the believers."
  15,89,"Say - O Messenger: I am indeed a warner of the punishment and I make clear that which will guide you."
  15,90,"I warn you of a punishment similar to that which Allah sent down on those who formed an alliance to deny the messengers."